# Refresh Navigation Invariant

When implementing navigation or URL-state changes, keep this invariant:

- After browser refresh/reload, the app must stay on the exact current URL (`pathname + search + hash`).
- Never redirect users to a previous page as a side effect of reload.
- This applies to all sections (`/`, `/listings`, `/listing/:id`, `/add-listing`, `/profile`, `/settings`, `/admin`, and user cabinet pages).

## Implementation Rules

- Do not use `history.back()` in logic that can run after reload.
- If closing overlays/modals represented in query params, prefer explicit URL cleanup with `replaceState` over back navigation in reload scenarios.
- Keep route initialization idempotent: reading URL is allowed; implicit navigation to another route is not.
- Avoid startup effects that rewrite route to a different page unless it is a strict auth guard.
- On protected pages, never redirect while auth is still loading/fetching (`isLoading || isFetching` must be false first).
- Missing JWT alone is not enough to force logout if cookie/session auth is still valid.
- On homepage reload, if `openListing` is present in query, clear it via `replaceState` so refresh stays on homepage content instead of reopening the last card.
- In user-cabinet routes (`moje inzeraty`), always preserve `userId` query param when applying/resetting filters so refresh never escapes to generic listings.

## Required Verification Before Deploy

- Refresh on each major page keeps the same URL.
- Refresh on opened listing/detail keeps that listing/detail.
- Refresh on homepage never jumps to previously visited page.
- Flow check: open listing card -> click `NNAuto` logo -> refresh homepage must not reopen that listing card.
- Flow check: in `moje inzeraty`, refresh and filter apply must keep `userId` and stay inside cabinet context.
- Refresh on `add-listing`, `moje inzeraty`, `profile`, and `settings` keeps user on the same page.
- Mobile and desktop behavior are identical.
